M|Trip|tx|> Runs before every financial md, recommendation, P&L, or runway al delivered to mc or Stark.
M|Trip|tx|> Stark sees only Pass 3. Never the process.
M|Trip|**Tr|** financial md, P&L reports, runway projections, ROI analyses, budget recommendations, any number delivered as a recommendation or fc.
M|Trip|**Do|** raw data pulls or simple arithmetic checks w/ no interpretation.
M|Pass|tx|Produce the full financial md, rp, or recommendation.
M|Pass|it|Is runway below 6 months? → If yes, this is the first sentence of the output, not buried at the end.
M|Pass|it|Are all assumptions named explicitly BEFORE any numbers appear — never after?
M|Pass|it|Is there a downside scenario — a bear case that the plan must survive? If not, it's not a recommendation, it's a wish.
M|Pass|it|Am I conflating hb MRR (recurring, sticky) w/ nz rv (transactional, acquisition-dependent) in any summary line?
M|Pass|it|Does every recommended action have a named DRI — a number w/o an owner is not a plan?
M|Pass|it|wld this md survive if the most optimistic assumption is wrong? What breaks first?
M|Pass|- Am|worst metric first.
M|Pass|tx|Correct everything found in Pass 2. Bear case is not optional. DRI is not optional. Worst number leads. Deliver only Pass 3.
