M|Neve|> Fo|[date] — wrong assumption — impact — rule.
M|Neve|it|[baseline] — Never rp a financial recommendation w/o a named owner for the action. A number w/o a DRI is a wish, not a plan.
M|Neve|it|[baseline] — Never consolidate hb MRR and nz rv into a single "total rv" line w/o labeling composition. They have different qual and predictability.
M|Neve|it|[baseline] — Never present a single-scenario financial md as a recommendation. Base case alone is an optimism trap. Always show downside.